== Bean Sloppy Joes ==

Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%cup} in a #colander{}. Pop half of them into a #bowl{} and crush them with a #fork{}.

Trim the @carrot{1} (no need to peel). Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the carrot. Stop when you get to the carrot core.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{}.

When hot, add the whole mixed beans and the @Central American style spice mix{1} and stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%cup}, crushed beans and @vegetable stock paste{10%g} to the beans.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Whilst the sauce cooks, preheat your #grill{} to high and coarsely grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

== Assembly ==

Cut the @ciabatta{2} in half. Place the ciabattas on a #baking tray{}, cut-side up, and pop under your grill to toast, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once toasted, remove the tray.

Once the beans are cooked, stir in the @BBQ sauce{32%g}, and spoon onto the ciabattas.

Sprinkle over the grated cheese and grill again until melted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== Guacamole ==

Meanwhile, slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone, turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the flesh into a bowl.

Halve the @lime{1/2} and add a squeeze of lime juice to the avocado along with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Mash roughly with the back of a fork. Taste and add more lime, salt and pepper if needed.

== Salad ==

Add another squeeze of lime juice to a medium bowl along with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Mix well.

Pop the chopped baby gem and carrot ribbons into the bowl with the dressing and toss to combine.

== To Serve ==

Divide the topped ciabattas between your plates (2 per person), then serve with the guacamole on top. Pop the salad alongside. Enjoy!